.\" Man page for Project 0x16. C - Simple Shell
.TH Simple Shell Manpage "12 August 2021" "version 1.0"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell - Simple UNIX command interpreter

simple_shell - simple_shell (hsh) is a simple and basic shell, command-lne
interpreter that provides you an interface to the Linux system, permi you
execute commands like shell (sh) console command.

Take input when you type a command and execute some functions based on that
input and show you the execution of that function in other words:
the output command.

.SH SYNOPSIS
The simple shell is a simplified version of  the original shell, written by
Ken Thompson

./hsh
/bin/[command] [option]
[command] [option]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Is a simple hsh command language interpreter that executes commands using the
path of this command that stored in the bin directory, the shell read from the
standard input through the getline command, is based on the shell designed by
Ken Thompson

.SH EXAMPLE
$  /bin/ls -l
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     510 Aug 17 19:39 brokentoken.c
  -rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   17264 Aug 17 13:37 shell
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root    1526 Aug 17 16:45 shell.c
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     615 Aug 18 11:37 simpleshell.h
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     728 Aug 14 18:50 match.c

$  ls -l
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     510 Aug 17 19:39 brokentoken.c
  -rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   17264 Aug 17 13:37 shell
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root    1526 Aug 17 16:45 shell.c
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     615 Aug 18 11:37 simpleshell.h
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     728 Aug 14 18:50 match.c

$ /bin/pwd
  /home/simple_shell

$ hhhhh
  ./shell: No such file or directory

.SH BUILTIN COMMANDS

.SS env
- list the current environment variables

.SS exit
- exit the shell

